From 0cd70b8f3cf2304d7b0bf7526a01cf5cbde4cdcd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aaron Paterson <apaterson@pm.me>
Date: Mon, 16 Mar 2026 12:09:13 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] odb: guard source-chain iterations against non-files backends

The odb_source vtable abstraction allows multiple backend
implementations, but 17 callsites iterate the source chain and
downcast every source to odb_source_files. This prevents adding
any non-files source to the chain (even as an alternate) without
hitting a BUG() assertion.

Change odb_source_files_downcast() to return NULL for non-files
source types instead of calling BUG(). Add NULL checks at all
iteration sites that downcast sources in loops:

  - loose.c: loose object map loading and lookup
  - midx.c: multi-pack-index access and cleanup
  - object-file.c: loose cache and reprepare
  - object-name.c: short object filename search
  - packfile.c: pack iteration, cache, and entry lookup
  - packfile.h: repo_for_each_pack iterator macros
  - commit-graph.c: packed object enumeration
  - builtin/cat-file.c: batch object iteration
  - builtin/fast-import.c: pack lookup
  - builtin/grep.c: pack preparation
  - builtin/pack-objects.c: pack enumeration and cache

Direct downcasts of odb->sources (the primary source, which is
always a files backend) and downcasts inside vtable callbacks
(which are only called for matching source types) are not
affected.

This is a prerequisite for pluggable ODB backends, following the
pattern established by the refs subsystem where the reftable
backend was enabled by first eliminating all ref backend
downcasts.

Signed-off-by: Aaron Paterson <apaterson@pm.me>
---
